## 1. What Is Agency OS

Agency OS is a **complete operating system for digital marketing agencies**, sold as a multi-tenant SaaS product. The person who builds and sells it — you — operates from a SuperAdmin layer that sits above all agency tenants.

Each agency that purchases the product gets their own isolated environment:
- Their own owner and employees
- Their own clients
- Only the modules they have paid for
- Complete data isolation from all other agencies

The platform has **four layers of users** (SuperAdmin, Agency Owner, Employee, Client) and **eleven feature modules** that agencies can purchase incrementally, each building on the previous.

### What makes it different

- **Self-hosted** — runs entirely on your own hardware. No AWS, no Vercel, no third-party SaaS fees beyond API keys. Your homelab runs the entire stack.
- **AI-native** — eleven LangGraph agents handle tasks that would otherwise require dedicated staff: scoring leads, generating reports, auditing communications, optimising ad campaigns, orchestrating outreach sequences.
- **Multi-tenant by design** — one codebase, one database, one backend serves every agency with full data isolation via `agency_id` row-level tenancy.
- **Module-gated** — agencies only see and access what they have paid for. One SQL toggle activates a module instantly.

