## 2. What Problem Does It Solve

### The agency problem

A typical digital marketing agency with 5-20 employees wastes 30-40% of its time on:

| Problem | Hours wasted per week |
|---|---|
| Manual client report generation | 8-12h |
| Tracking employee attendance and tasks | 4-6h |
| Chasing client approvals for content | 3-5h |
| Manual payroll calculation | 3-4h |
| CRM updates after deals close | 2-3h |
| Monitoring ad campaigns for anomalies | 5-8h |
| Personalising cold outreach | 4-6h |
| Competitive research | 3-5h |

Agency OS eliminates or drastically reduces all of these through automation and AI.

### The tool fragmentation problem

Most agencies use 10-15 disconnected tools: Slack, Notion, Trello, HubSpot, Google Sheets for payroll, WhatsApp for client approval, email for reports, Buffer for scheduling, and a different dashboard per ad platform.

Agency OS replaces all of these with a single platform where **every data point is connected**. The EOM scoring agent can factor in client satisfaction signals from communications. The churn agent can read performance data from reports. The outreach agent can pull competitor intelligence gathered by the research agent. All from one shared database.

### The margin problem

Selling Agency OS to agencies on a monthly retainer gives you predictable recurring revenue while agencies get a tool that replaces multiple subscriptions and saves 30+ hours per month.

