## 4. User Roles Explained

### SuperAdmin (You)

- **Access**: `admin.yourdomain.com` or `/superadmin` route
- **Credentials**: Hardcoded in `.env` as `SUPERADMIN_EMAIL` and `SUPERADMIN_PASSWORD`. Never stored in the database.
- **Can do**: Create agencies, activate/deactivate modules, view all tenants' data, monitor all AI agents system-wide, manage billing records
- **Cannot see**: Their own account from the agency owner's perspective

**First login flow:**
```
Open https://app.yourdomain.com
Enter superadmin email + password from .env
→ Redirected to /superadmin
→ Create first agency via "New Agency" button
→ Agency owner gets their credentials
```

### Agency Owner

- **Access**: `/owner` route after login
- **Credentials**: Created by SuperAdmin via `POST /superadmin/agencies`
- **Can do**: Everything within their agency — create employees, create clients, assign tasks, run payroll, trigger AI agents, see all reports and communications
- **Cannot see**: Other agencies, SuperAdmin layer, other employees' payslips

**First owner login flow:**
```
SuperAdmin creates the agency and sets owner email/password
Owner logs in at https://app.yourdomain.com
→ Redirected to /owner
→ Sees their dashboard with modules that SuperAdmin activated
→ First step: create geofence zones (Settings) and add employees
```

### Employee

- **Access**: `/employee` route after login
- **Credentials**: Created by Agency Owner via `POST /employees`
- **Can do**: Clock in/out, view and update their tasks, see their own clients, send client communications, download their own payslips
- **Cannot see**: Other employees' data, payroll figures, financial information, AI agent logs

**Employee first use:**
```
Owner creates employee account with email + password
Employee logs in at https://app.yourdomain.com
→ Redirected to /employee
→ First action: tap "Clock In" on the Attendance page
→ Browser requests GPS location
→ If within geofence zone: clocked in
→ If outside zone: rejection message with distance to nearest zone
```

### Client

- **Access**: `/client` route after login
- **Credentials**: Created when owner creates a client record and enables portal access
- **Can do**: View their campaign reports, approve or reject content drafts, see their invoices, communicate with account team
- **Cannot see**: Other clients, any internal agency data, employee information

