## 5. Module Architecture

Modules must be purchased and activated in dependency order. Each module builds on the infrastructure of the previous one.

### M1 — Workforce Intelligence (Foundation)
**Required for all other modules.**

**What it does:**
- **Geofenced attendance** — employees clock in via GPS on their phone. The backend calculates the Haversine distance between their coordinates and each office zone. If within radius: session opens. Clock-out calculates hours worked automatically.
- **Task dispatch** — owner creates tasks with title, description, priority (low/medium/high/urgent), deadline, and assigned employee. Tasks move through: `created → in_progress → submitted → verified/rejected`. Every status change is logged to `task_status_history`.
- **Payroll generation** — at end of month, system aggregates attendance records for each employee, calculates gross pay (fixed salary or hours × rate), applies deductions/allowances, and generates a professional PDF payslip via WeasyPrint.
- **Communication logging** — every email or WhatsApp message sent from an employee to a client is tagged and stored. Inbound replies are captured via webhooks.
- **EOM scoring** — on the 1st of each month at 02:00 IST, a LangGraph agent scores every employee on task performance (on-time rate, first-pass rate) and client satisfaction (Claude sentiment analysis of inbound messages). Owner reviews before publishing.
- **Compliance audit** — nightly Claude scan of all outbound messages. Flags personal contact sharing, off-platform redirect attempts, and unauthorised pricing discussions.

**Celery jobs:** `flag_incomplete_sessions` (23:00 IST), `send_deadline_reminders` (09:00 IST), `escalate_overdue_tasks` (hourly), `audit_communications` (02:00 IST)

---

### M2 — Operations Core
**Requires M1.**

**What it does:**
- **Client onboarding** — when a HubSpot deal closes, n8n fires a webhook. The OnboardingGraph LangGraph agent generates a structured client brief using Claude, sends a welcome email, creates a kickoff calendar invite (stub), updates the client record, and notifies the account manager.
- **Invoice generation** — owner creates invoices with line items and GST. WeasyPrint generates a professional PDF. Invoice status tracking: draft → sent → paid/overdue.
- **HubSpot sync** — deal stage changes in HubSpot trigger real-time updates to the platform via n8n webhooks.

**LangGraph agent:** `OnboardingGraph` (4 nodes: generate_brief → send_email → update_crm → notify_am)

---

### M3 — Insights & Reporting Agent
**Requires M2.**

**What it does:**
- Pulls live campaign data from GA4, Meta Ads Manager, and Google Ads APIs
- Pandas processes raw metrics into standardised format
- Claude generates a human-quality narrative: performance summary, key wins, areas of concern, recommended next actions
- WeasyPrint assembles branded PDF report
- Delivered to client via Gmail + WhatsApp
- Follow-up loop: if no client reply in 48h, drafts a nudge for AM review

**Per-client config:** Schedule (weekly/monthly), platforms, KPI targets (ROAS, CTR, CPC)

**Stub behaviour:** If API credentials are missing, returns realistic sample data so the full pipeline can be tested.

**LangGraph agent:** `ReportingAgent` (6 nodes: pull_data → process_metrics → generate_narrative → assemble_pdf → deliver → monitor_reply)

---

### M4 — Churn Prevention Agent
**Requires M3.**

**What it does:**
- Daily scan of every active client across all M4-enabled agencies
- Collects signals from three categories:
  - **Performance signals** (from M3 reports): ROAS decline, CTR drop, consecutive period degradation
  - **Engagement signals** (from M1 comms): reduced inbound frequency, days since last message, sentiment trends
  - **Operational signals** (from M2): overdue invoices, stalled tasks
- Claude evaluates all signals and produces a score 0-100 with a rationale
- If score ≥ threshold (default 40): creates a `ChurnAlert` record, updates client status to `at_risk`, notifies owner
- If M6 (Research Agent) is active: enriches alert with competitor intelligence

**Alert resolution:** Owner marks as `resolved` or `false_positive`. Client reverts to `active` when all alerts are closed.

---

### M5 — Campaign Task Manager
**Requires M2.**

**What it does:**
- Separate from M1 tasks — M5 is about **what content gets produced for clients**, not employee accountability
- Campaign → Campaign Tasks pipeline: `brief → in_progress → draft → review → approved → scheduled → live`
- When task reaches `approved`: automatically calls Buffer REST API to schedule the post
- Links to M3 (reports reference what was produced) and M10 (performance monitoring after going live)

---

### M6 — Research Agent
**Requires M2.**

**What it does:**
- Owner adds competitors to track per client (with Meta page ID and domain)
- Weekly scan pulls data from:
  - **Meta Ad Library API** — active ads, estimated spend, creative formats
  - **SerpAPI** — Google organic rankings, active paid ads, brand snippets
- Claude synthesises raw data into a structured competitive intelligence brief with 5 sections: overview, advertising strategy, key changes, threat assessment, counter-strategies
- Brief stored in **Qdrant** as a vector — M4 (churn enrichment) and M8 (outreach personalisation) can retrieve relevant context via semantic search
- Owner sees a feed of all generated briefs, filterable by client or industry

**Qdrant collection:** `research_briefs` — 768-dim embeddings (nomic-embed-text or hash stub)

---

### M7 — Lead Analyst Agent
**Requires M2.**

**What it does:**
- Owner defines the agency's **Ideal Client Profile (ICP)** in natural language: ideal industries, company size, ad budget range, decision-maker title, pain points, disqualifiers
- Leads arrive via: manual entry, HubSpot webhook (via n8n), or direct API
- LangGraph agent: loads lead data → loads ICP → Claude scores lead 0-100 → writes back to HubSpot → creates follow-up task for AE → notifies owner
- Lead dashboard sorted by score descending — highest-fit leads appear first
- Hourly Celery job scores any unscored leads automatically

---

### M8 — Personalisation & Outreach Agent
**Requires M6 + M7.**

**What it does:**
- For a given lead, retrieves: ICP score and rationale (M7), competitor intelligence for their vertical (M6 Qdrant search)
- Claude writes a **3-step personalised outreach sequence**:
  - Step 1 (day 0): Personalised cold email referencing competitor intel
  - Step 2 (day 3): LinkedIn message (shorter, conversational)
  - Step 3 (day 7): Follow-up with case study angle
- Two send modes:
  - **Manual**: AE reviews each step before it goes out
  - **Auto**: steps send on schedule without intervention
- Reply detection: when Gmail polling detects a reply, sequence pauses and AE is notified

---

### M9 — ABM Orchestrator
**Requires M8.**

**What it does:**
- Account-based marketing for the agency's highest-priority target accounts
- Journey state machine: `identified → researching → first_touch → engaged → proposal → closed_won | closed_lost`
- LangGraph agent evaluates account state, recommends next touch (channel + type + timing), generates content, routes to channel, logs touch, and advances stage if conditions met
- Multi-channel: email, LinkedIn, WhatsApp, calls/meetings
- Account intelligence feed sorted by days stale — most neglected accounts surface first
- Weekly Celery job: reviews all stale accounts (7+ days no touch) and runs orchestration

---

### M10 — Optimisation & Prediction Engine
**Requires M3 + M5.**

**What it does:**
- Pulls last 7 days of live campaign data from Meta and Google Ads
- Compares metrics to KPI targets — identifies performance gaps with severity ratings
- Claude generates ranked list of specific recommendations (pause underperforming ads, reallocate budgets, adjust bids) with confidence scores and rationale

**Two modes:**
- **Advisory (default)**: recommendations delivered to AM via Slack. AM approves each individually. Nothing happens automatically.
- **Autonomous (opt-in per client)**: approved change types execute directly via ad platform APIs within guardrails (max budget change %, max bid change %, minimum daily budget). Kill switch disables instantly.

**Predictive alerts:** Daily trajectory analysis projects end-of-month performance. If a KPI is on track to miss target, raises a `PredictiveAlert` with severity (warning/critical) and days remaining.

---

### M11 — Campaign Orchestration Platform
**Requires M5 + M10.**

**What it does:**
- Owner or employee creates a **content brief** (objective, audience, key message, tone, platform, content type, word limit)
- Claude generates N variations (default 3), each with a different creative angle (Emotional, Feature-led, Urgency)
- Owner selects the best draft and submits for client approval
- Client approves via:
  - **Portal**: logs into Dashboard 3, clicks Approve or Request Changes
  - **WhatsApp**: replies "APPROVE" or "REJECT - feedback" to WATI message
- On approval: automatically schedules via Buffer REST API, updates M5 campaign task to `scheduled`
- Performance feedback loop: M10 monitors published content performance, M3 includes it in next report

