## 7. System Architecture

### Development architecture

```
YOUR MAC (development)
├── FastAPI (uvicorn --reload, port 8000)
├── Celery worker
├── React/Vite (port 5173)
│
│  ← Tailscale VPN →
│
HOMELAB LAPTOP
├── PostgreSQL :5432
├── Redis :6379
├── Qdrant :6333
└── n8n :5678

Mac calls homelab services via Tailscale IP.
n8n calls FastAPI via Mac's Tailscale IP.
```

### Production architecture

```
INTERNET
    │ HTTPS
    ▼
nginx (app VM)
├── app.domain.com → React build (static files)
└── api.domain.com → FastAPI :8000

App VM (Proxmox)
├── Docker: agencyos_api
├── Docker: agencyos_celery_worker
└── Docker: agencyos_celery_beat

Data VM (homelab, connected via Tailscale)
├── PostgreSQL :5432
├── Redis :6379
├── Qdrant :6333
└── n8n :5678
```

### Database tenancy model

Every single table that stores agency data has `agency_id UUID NOT NULL` as a column and foreign key to `agencies.id`. The API layer enforces this in every query:

```python
# Every query looks like this — never just select(Task)
query = select(Task).where(
    Task.agency_id == current_user.agency_id
)
```

There is no shared data between agencies except:
- `agencies` table (agency names only, readable by SuperAdmin)
- `agency_modules` table (which modules are active)

