## 10. Production Deployment

### Server requirements

| Resource | Minimum | Recommended |
|---|---|---|
| CPU | 2 cores | 4 cores |
| RAM | 4 GB | 8 GB |
| Disk | 20 GB | 50 GB |
| OS | Ubuntu 22.04 | Ubuntu 24.04 |

### Full production setup

**Step 1 — Install dependencies on app VM:**
```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y docker.io docker-compose-plugin nginx \
    certbot python3-certbot-nginx git curl nodejs npm
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER && newgrp docker
```

**Step 2 — Deploy code:**
```bash
sudo mkdir -p /opt/agencyos/{media,backups/postgres,backups/qdrant,logs}
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/agencyos
cd /opt/agencyos
git clone https://github.com/YOURUSER/agencyos.git .
```

**Step 3 — Configure environment:**
```bash
cp backend/.env.production backend/.env
nano backend/.env   # Fill all REPLACE_WITH_* values
```

**Step 4 — Run migrations:**
```bash
cd backend
python3 -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
alembic upgrade head
deactivate
```

**Step 5 — Build and start Docker services:**
```bash
cd /opt/agencyos/infra
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d
curl http://localhost:8000/health   # Should return OK
```

**Step 6 — Build frontend:**
```bash
cd /opt/agencyos/frontend
echo "VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1" > .env.production
npm install && npm run build
```

**Step 7 — Configure nginx + SSL:**
```bash
sudo cp infra/nginx/agencyos.conf /etc/nginx/sites-available/agencyos
sudo sed -i 's/yourdomain.com/YOURACTUALDOMAIN.com/g' /etc/nginx/sites-available/agencyos
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/agencyos /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/agencyos
# DNS A records must be live before running certbot:
sudo certbot --nginx -d app.domain.com -d api.domain.com
sudo systemctl enable nginx && sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

**Step 8 — Verify production:**
```bash
curl https://api.yourdomain.com/health          # → {"status":"ok","env":"production"}
curl -I https://app.yourdomain.com              # → HTTP/2 200
docker ps                                        # All 3 containers running
docker logs agencyos_api --tail=20              # No errors
```

### Updating production

```bash
cd /opt/agencyos
git pull origin main

# Rebuild and restart backend
cd infra
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

# Apply any new migrations
docker exec agencyos_api alembic upgrade head

# Rebuild frontend if changed
cd /opt/agencyos/frontend
npm run build
# nginx serves new dist/ immediately
```

