## 16. Celery Tasks Reference

All scheduled times are in IST (UTC+5:30).

| Task name | Schedule | Queue | What it does |
|---|---|---|---|
| `m1_tasks.flag_incomplete_sessions` | Daily 23:00 IST | m1 | Finds open attendance sessions from today, marks incomplete, notifies owner |
| `m1_tasks.send_deadline_reminders` | Daily 09:00 IST | m1 | Tasks due within 24h that aren't submitted — reminds employee |
| `m1_tasks.escalate_overdue_tasks` | Every hour | m1 | Tasks past deadline in created/in_progress — marks overdue, alerts owner |
| `m1_tasks.audit_communications` | Daily 02:00 IST | agents | Claude scans today's outbound messages for compliance violations |
| `m3_tasks.run_scheduled_reports` | Daily 08:00 IST | m3 | Checks which clients are due a report, runs ReportingAgent for each |
| `m3_tasks.schedule_report_followup` | 48h after delivery | m3 | If no client reply, drafts follow-up nudge for AM |
| `m4_tasks.run_churn_scan` | Daily 07:00 IST | m4 | Runs ChurnRiskAgent for every active client in M4-enabled agencies |
| `m6_tasks.run_research_scan` | Monday 06:00 IST | m6 | Generates competitive intelligence for all tracked competitors |
| `m7_tasks.score_unscored_leads` | Every hour | m7 | Finds leads with status=new and runs LeadScoringAgent |
| `m8_tasks.send_scheduled_steps` | Every hour | m8 | Sends outreach sequence steps that are due and approved |
| `m9_tasks.run_abm_weekly_review` | Monday 07:00 IST | m9 | Reviews stale ABM accounts and runs orchestration |
| `m10_tasks.run_daily_optimisation` | Daily 10:00 IST | m10 | Runs OptimisationAgent for all clients with M10 config |
| `m10_tasks.run_trajectory_monitor` | Daily 18:00 IST | m10 | Projects end-of-month performance, raises PredictiveAlerts |
| `m11_tasks.send_approval_reminders` | Every 6 hours | m11 | Nudges clients who haven't responded to content approval requests |

**Manually triggering any task:**
```bash
# Development
celery -A celery_worker.celery_app call app.tasks.m1_tasks.flag_incomplete_sessions

# Or via Python
python -c "
from celery_worker import celery_app
celery_app.send_task('app.tasks.m3_tasks.run_scheduled_reports')
print('Task queued')"
```

