## 17. LangGraph Agents Reference

| Agent | Module | Nodes | Trigger |
|---|---|---|---|
| EOM Scoring Agent | M1 | task_data_aggregation → sentiment_scoring → score_combination → narrative_generation → owner_notification | 1st of month 02:00 IST |
| Communication Audit Agent | M1 | scan_messages → claude_evaluation → flag_violations | Daily 02:00 IST |
| Onboarding Orchestration Agent | M2 | generate_brief → send_email → update_crm → notify_am | HubSpot webhook or manual trigger |
| Reporting Agent | M3 | pull_data → process_metrics → generate_narrative → assemble_pdf → deliver → monitor_reply | Scheduled or manual |
| Churn Risk Agent | M4 | fetch_signals → score_risk → enrich_with_research → generate_alert → notify | Daily 07:00 IST or manual |
| Competitive Research Agent | M6 | fetch_competitor_ads → fetch_serp_data → synthesise_brief → store_vectors → deliver | Weekly Monday or manual |
| Lead Scoring Agent | M7 | intake_lead → fetch_context → score_against_icp → write_back_hubspot → create_task → notify | On lead creation or hourly |
| Outreach Personalisation Agent | M8 | retrieve_context → generate_messages → create_sequence → send_first_step → monitor_replies | Manual trigger per lead |
| ABM Orchestration Agent | M9 | evaluate_state → recommend_next_touch → generate_content → route_channel → log_touch → update_journey | Weekly or manual per account |
| Campaign Optimisation Agent | M10 | pull_live_data → analyse_gaps → generate_recommendations → get_approval → execute_changes → confirm | Daily 10:00 IST or manual |
| Content Generation Agent | M11 | parse_brief → generate_drafts → create_approval_requests → notify_client → monitor_response | Manual trigger per brief |

**All agents write their state to PostgreSQL at each node** — if an agent fails mid-run, you can inspect the DB to see exactly which node it completed last. For example, an `OnboardingFlow` row has a `last_completed_node` field that shows the last successful step.

**Viewing agent run logs in production:**
```bash
# Search FastAPI logs for a specific agent
docker logs agencyos_api 2>&1 | grep "\[Onboarding\]"
docker logs agencyos_api 2>&1 | grep "\[Lead\]"
docker logs agencyos_api 2>&1 | grep "\[Content\]"
```

