## 21. Upgrading and Migrations

### Adding a new model field

```python
# 1. Add field to the model in models/yourmodel.py
new_field: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(String(255), nullable=True)

# 2. Generate migration
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add new_field to yourmodel"

# 3. Review the generated migration file in alembic/versions/
# Make sure it looks correct — Alembic sometimes misses things

# 4. Apply migration
alembic upgrade head

# 5. If production: run on prod server
docker exec agencyos_api alembic upgrade head
```

### Rolling back a migration

```bash
# Roll back one step
alembic downgrade -1

# Roll back to specific revision
alembic downgrade abc123

# Roll back to beginning (development only — destroys all data)
alembic downgrade base
```

### Viewing migration history

```bash
alembic history --verbose
alembic current   # Shows what version the DB is at
```

