```bash
# View backup directory
ls -lh /opt/agencyos/backups/postgres/
# Files: agencyos_20260413_020000.sql.gz

# Check backup size (should be > 0)
du -sh /opt/agencyos/backups/postgres/agencyos_*.sql.gz | tail -5
```

### Manual backup

```bash
PGPASSWORD=your_db_password pg_dump \
  -h DB_HOST -U agencyos_user -d agencyos \
  --format=plain | gzip > /tmp/manual_backup_$(date +%Y%m%d).sql.gz
```

### Restore from backup

```bash
# WARNING: This overwrites the current database
gunzip < /opt/agencyos/backups/postgres/agencyos_TIMESTAMP.sql.gz | \
  PGPASSWORD=your_db_password psql \
  -h DB_HOST -U agencyos_user -d agencyos
```

